5:
Who's that? Isn't she a bit young to be
out here alone?
24: Shh, you're safe now. Are you okay?
29:
Ye—sniffle—yesh... Thank you both
for saving me.
34:
Let's get you out of here. Get up nice and
slowly, now. There you go.
38:
Wait, you were looking for information?
Alone? In the Kaleidoscope?!
41:
You have guts, but a bit more caution
would serve you well.
44:
In the stories, a dashing young
adventurer always arrives in the nick
of time to save the day, but...
You're absolutely right.
48:
I don't know about the dashing part,
but I'm glad we were able to help.
54: T-that's not true! You were very heroic!
56:
You carved right through those
monsters— No fear, no hesitation!
Adventurers are sooo cool!
59: Wow, gosh, you really think so?
63:
That aside, what information were you
seeking? We'd be happy to help,
if we can.
67: See, I'm trying to be a better journalist.
69:
I just started writing for a magazine
called the Oculus. The other writers are
nice, but I'm done being the baby of the
team...
70:
I want to be a really good journalist who
can work all on my own. Someone the
others can depend on too!
72:
S-so I figured if I wrote a jaw-dropping,
show-stopping article, maybe, just
maybe... Y'know?
76: What you need is practice, then.
82:
No one learns to wield a sword with just
one swing. The pen is no different.
86:
You don't need to throw yourself in at
the deep end! In my experience as
a cook, sometimes the simplest things
come out the best.
91: Yeah, you guys are right! I'll do my best!
95:
Bu-but... I can't start writing without a
scoop to write about. What should I do?
100:
Just finished the interview! One of them
said she has trouble drying her laundry
because her veranda is shady.
105:
Hmm, doing the laundry in smaller
loads should help. The less crowded
clothes are on the clothesline, the faster
they'll dry!
110: Ooh! I'll add that in, Alk!
114:
An article on "everyday life-hacks," was
it? I'm sure readers will find it helpful.
117:
Wow, Luluca! Is that the last page of
your notebook? You've written down
a TON of ideas!
123:
Ahaha, I sure did talk to a lot of people,
after all!
125:
Once I get back, I'll ask the other
journalists for tips on condensing
interviews into clear, concise writing!
129:
That sounds like a great plan! I'm sure
they've got plenty of great advice,
so never hesitate to ask for it!
132:
Thank you so much for the help!
I don't know what I would've done
without you!
137:
I've gotta run, but keep your eyes peeled
for next month's issue of the Oculus!
141:
Wowie, everyone's talking about the
latest edition of the Oculus! No wonder
the Guild sold out so fast!
144:
It has a lifestyle guide addressing
everyday issues. The advice within is
great for solo adventurers, apparently.
148:
Everyone's got chores to do, after all.
Who wouldn't appreciate some tips
and tricks?
151:
Ooh, that must be the one our staff's
been gushing about. The Guild is
actually looking into getting more
copies printed!
156:
The PR team keeps saying they HAVE to
meet the author. They talked my ear off
about what a phenomenal writer she is!
160: Wow, really? Did you hear that, Luluca?
164: Oh, shucks, it wasn't ALL me!
169:
It's all thanks to the help and advice
I got from everyone along the way!
170:
There may only be one writer, but more
people work on a single article than
you'd think.
175:
Knowing so many people depend on
me is all the motivation I could ever
need!
179:
That's so sweet! I'll be looking forward
to more great work from the Oculus!
185: Y-yes, I'll do my very best!
189:
Hey, Luluca. If you're interested, I know
a really great small-town library with
books from all over the place!
194:
Light and I live right nearby, so you'd
always know where to find us if you
need any help. Do you want to visit it,
some time?
